18:
What a wonderful display from our
entrants! That wraps up our
spur-of-the-moment brawl! The
Guild will now present the
combatants with their hard-earned
rewards!
22:
And just a reminder! The joint
graduation ceremony will be
starting momentarily. All grads,
make your way to the stage!
31:
I'm sure they'll make it in time.
Knowing Nao, though, she'll
definitely be cutting it close.
36:
I'm really starting to get worried...
They were supposed to be back by
yesterday, but—oh no! They're about
to call us any second now!
52:
After your long journey, you finally
made it. You're here, and I couldn't
be more proud of you. Best of luck to
you on your next adventure.
65:
Nao Nagihara, present and
accounted for! I'm back from my
mission and RIGHT on time!
69:
Ugh... In what world would this be
considered "on time"?
85:
To think the day would come where
we could all be here on this
beautiful spring morning,
celebrating our graduation... This all
feels like a dream.
89:
It is a true honor to stand before you
all now, representing the students of
Shibuya for our joint graduation
ceremony.
92:
All of us have overcome incredible
hardships to be here today. There
were times when we all came
together, working hand in hand...
97:
...and times when we've never felt
more divided and alone. Times
when we prayed for a savior. And
times when that savior never came.
100:
And in that darkness, I told myself
over and over that I shouldn't cry.
That crying wouldn't solve anything.
111:
Because when I did—when I finally
reached out for help—there was
someone who took my hand and
never let go.
114:
Someone who stayed with me
through it all and led me out of that
darkness. You taught me that it's
okay to cry.
117:
It's a fact of life that, sometimes,
things won't go your way. That the
world won't listen to your pleas.
120:
Maybe you'll feel as though you're
stuck. Like nothing you do will ever
make a difference.
124:
But sometimes, it's enough just to
know that we're not alone. And if
someone in your life is stuck, you
can be that voice beside them that
says, "I'm here."
127:
That unity, that love, holds the power
to change worlds. It certainly
changed mine.
131:
Because when we're together, we
shine all the brighter.
134:
That's why, no matter how dark this
world may get, I'll never let that go.
143:
Thank you for protecting us. For
standing beside us. For loving us
with every fiber of your being.
147:
I'll take the warmth, the strength you
gave me... and carry it with me
always.
151:
Until the day comes when we can
be together again.
154:
So... Yup! That about covers the
mushy part!
157:
By the way, the Abyss Exploration
Team is recruiting new members!
161:
If anyone is interested in joining up,
feel free to talk to me after the
ceremony! We'll be waiting for you
with open arms!
170:
Now THAT was an awesome
graduation ceremony. I was on the
edge of my seat—I thought for sure
Nao wasn't gonna make it!
174:
Your speech blew me away. Did you
make that up on the spot?
179:
Heh heh... I'll leave that up to your
imagination!
186:
I just wanted to say congratulations.
You did it.
191:
Thanks, Yumu. Congratulations to
you, too.
194:
I wish Mr. Takamori was with us.
Apparently he had to go straight
from graduation to preparing for the
commencement ceremony... Being
an adult sounds rough.
198:
Hey, anyone seen Kageoka? He's in
our graduating class, right? I was
gonna ask him about his plans.
203:
Ryuichi told me that he doesn't have
anything in mind yet.
213:
Yes. Tohru said something similar.
"No new plans for now."
216:
However, Dedalia and Sha Suzu told
me that they're going to work for
PBC.
220:
Now that you mention it, that kind of
work sounds right up their alley...
223:
But, wow... Working in another world?
I didn't even consider that.
227:
What about you, Ayumu? Don't you
have another VERY important
decision to make?
231: Y'know, matters of the heart and all—
239:
Wait, what? You mean you actually
have someone in mind?!
248:
Now this sounds like a fun
conversation! Let me in on this, guys!
252:
Stella, are you going to continue
your work as Keeper of Starview
Village?
257:
I am. And there's one other thing I've
decided to do. Something very
important.
260: ...But I can't tell you just yet.
265:
What?! I can't believe our Stella is
hiding something from us...
269:
I'll be ready to tell you once I finish
the book.
274:
I can't wait! How many pages do
you have left?
